					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/smapti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(362048); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=362048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251065" alt="Smapti" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=362048)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/smapti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(362048); return false;" >Smapti</a></span> <span class="odate time_1334749003 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Apr 2012 11:36</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1419600">
									

<p>I've actually never played any of the Silent Hill games.</p>
<p>My original concept for the creature, in line with the junk data aspect I mentioned earlier, was for it to be a pixellated blob and have bits and pieces sticking out all over the place. I couldn't find a way to describe that that sounded dry and clinical enough, so I went with pseudopods instead, because <em>everyone</em> loves pseudopods. The fact that the photographs came out corrupted, and the radio static noise (which isn't necessarily coming from the same kind of creature as the corpse was), are leftover elements from that.</p>

							</div>

								
