					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/howell2010" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1235453); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1235453&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251065" alt="howell2010" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1235453)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/howell2010" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1235453); return false;" >howell2010</a></span> <span class="odate time_1345111570 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Aug 2012 10:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1538980">
									

<p>I'm not attempting to necro this, I just want to answer this question because while reading, that term really bugged me.</p>
<p>Memory Dump would be acceptable for my enjoyment.</p>
<p>and &quot;Divide by zero&quot; errors is too colloquial for me as well.</p>
<p>Certain redactions are really annoying to me as well, and indicate laziness(to me)</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Food was found to be fresh and edible, though unusually high in compounds known to cause [REDACTED].</p>
</blockquote>
<p>It is better reading if the compound was named, or left redacted but had at least one symptom mentioned. Otherwise it reads like &quot;Food was found to be fresh and edible, though unusually high in compounds known to cause cats to gather and re-enact the Battle of Gettysburg.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The final photo showed a [REDACTED].</p>
</blockquote>
<p>a view so beautiful that we couldn't mention it for fear of creating a cognitohazard?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Survivor was highly confused about what had happened during the time contact was lost and the S&amp;R team located him, only repeating that [REDACTED]</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Only repeating &quot;Popeye's chicken is the shit!&quot;<br />
Also would be better sentence structure to say &quot;highly confused about what had happened between the time contact was lost and when the S&amp;R team located him&quot;</p>
<p>Other things that bother me are&#8230;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Plant samples were found to exhibit an abnormally high amount of mutation.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>What kind of mutation?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>█████████, several thousand kilometers away.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That one I just find strange. Several thousand km away from where?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Canvassing of the area proved unable to locate the owner/s of the vehicle prior to abandoning SCP-1165 for the day due to impending twilight.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Am I missing where it said to not be in 1165 after dark? Cause some of the later distances surely would take more time that possible to travel there and back before dark.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>leaning against a wall in an alleyway, the skeletal remains of an adult male</p>
</blockquote>
<p>He was standing up?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The remains of ██████'s wife and children, aged 9, 5, and 8 months,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>His wife is 9 years old? o.0 and has 2 kids aged 5 and 8 months? o.0 So she had a child when she was 4? o.0<br />
Or, did he have 3 kids and you just didn't mention his wife's age? And how would the foundation know exactly how old the children were if the father was just a skeleton?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>After 7 minutes without reaching the ground, pilot and support team committed suicide by gunshot.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Only 7 minutes? Pansies.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The corpse was nude except for a pair of black slacks.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>First, it would probably sound more clinical to say body. At least right here.<br />
Second&#8230; The body was nude except for being clothed? I think you should find a way to say it without using the word nude, because it isn't nude it is clothed.</p>
<p>That's all the major things.</p>
<p>The rest is just the tone. It doesn't feel clinical enough, or like a debrief.</p>
<p>I love the idea of this SCP. These are my favorite kind of SCPs, but this one isn't done well&#8230;<br />
I'm holding my upvote until the tone is fixed.</p>
<p>I won't downvote though, cause I see potential.</p>

							</div>

								
