			<div class="content" id="post-content-3570366">
									

<p>Just wanted to say that I disagree with most of these points, at least those about &quot;REDACTED&quot; usage.</p>
<p>I used my imagination, and enjoyed it a lot. Don't know what more to say about that..</p>
<p>That being said, I agree on a few things. The gangster against the wall is one. I imagine he was on <em>the ground</em> leaning against the wall, but the original quote is too ambiguous here. At first it sounds like he's standing up while leaning against the wall as a skeleton, which makes no sense neither technically nor &quot;lore&quot;-logically..</p>
<blockquote>
<p>aged 9, 5, and 8 months</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Sentence needs restructuring indeed.</p>
<p>Now to quote howell2010, who I replied to:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Only 7 minutes? Pansies.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't get it. What is your logic here? Keep falling (and bouncing) forever OR waiting for yourself to get smashed into pulp, given solid ground eventually appeared? Also, how is logical reasoning related to <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">bravery</span> &quot;bravery&quot; ?</p>
<p>The slacks: A bit annoyed by the nitpicking but I also think you're right. A better sentence would be &quot;(&#8230;) pair of black slacks as the only discernable clothing(&#8230;)&quot;</p>
<p>Anyways, enjoyed the read. An interesting world for sure, it in some way remind me of a computer generated world, with world &quot;edges&quot; (which makes you potentially fall forever, original map disappearing further into the distance) and backdrops that never get closer.</p>

