														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1943713">
									

<p>This is one of the more disturbing things I have read on this site.</p>
<p>This kind of idea is right up my alley (awful pun intended). It reminds me of the <a href="http://www.mariowiki.com/Minus_World">&quot;Minus World&quot; in Super Mario Bros</a>&#8230; i.e. a place that was not actually designed, and that no one was ever supposed to go&#8230; a place that just popped into existence by itself, via corruption of existing data.</p>
<p>I always found the Mario &quot;Minus World&quot; mildly disturbing for that very reason (it's a playable video game level, yet no one actually designed it)&#8230; I find this file disturbing for the same reason, only this one is much, much worse, for obvious reasons.</p>
<p>Well done. Enthusiastic +1 (for both the original file and the survey reports)</p>
<p>Edit: one very minor complaint - I agree with everyone else about the &quot;psuedopods&quot; - it just doesn't fit the feel of the rest of the file.</p>

